<body>

  <!-- HOW TO HELP -->
  <section id="help">
    <h2>How to Help</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">

      <!-- Donations & Money -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Donate Funds</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Donating to credible international or local organizations functioning in Turkey.  Verify credentials and transparency.</li>
          <li>Specify whether the donation is for <strong>emergency relief</strong> (food, water, shelter) or <strong>recovery efforts</strong> (school repairs, building strengthening).</li>
          <li>Participating in <strong>community fundraisers</strong> or campaigns that directly benefit rebuilding efforts in Turkey.</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.globalgiving.org/projects/turkey-earthquake-relief-fund/" target="_blank" class="donate-btn">Donate Now</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Volunteering & Skills -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Ways to Volunteer</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Volunteering with official groups and organizations that undertake thorough needs assessments.</li>
          <li>Contributing your professional experience, such as medical care, engineering, translation, or logistics, to help communities more effectively.</li>
          <li>Support local events like school drives, charity runs, and donation tables.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Information Sharing -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Spread Awareness</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Share trustworthy planning and safety information, including Turkish-language locations.</li>
          <li>Teach Turkish populations how to react prior to, during, and following aftershocks..</li>
          <li>Promote awareness-raising social media efforts.</li>
          <li>Provide explicit evacuation and emergency contact information in both English and Turkish.</li>
          <li>Encourage families to make emergency communication and reuniting plans.</li> 
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Crisis Phases -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Crisis Stages</h3>
        <details>
          <summary><strong>Emergency Phase</strong> — first hours/weeks</summary>
          <ul>
            <li>Having immediate access to water, shelter, food, etc.</li>
            <li>Medical assistance and first aid being on hand.</li>
            <li>Evacuation support and temporary housing accesible for the community.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><strong>Recovery Phase</strong> — months/years</summary>
          <ul>
            <li>Homes, schools, and infrastructure are rebuilt with assistance from the community.</li>
            <li>Strengthening buildings for earthquake resilience.</li>
            <li>Providing mental health support and long-term community programs.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary><strong>Preparedness Phase</strong> — before an emergency</summary>
          <ul>
            <li>Developing emergency plans for families and communities.</li>
            <li>Creating and updating disaster supply kits.</li>
            <li>Training volunteers in first aid, CPR, and emergency response.</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

